fields.description:
MuscleTech Nitro-Tech Protein
THE MOST POWERFUL PROTEIN FORMULA EVER DEVELOPED!

HOW IT WORKS
NITRO-TECH® is a scientifically engineered whey protein formula, and is enhanced with the most studied form of creatine for even better gains in muscle and strength. It also features whey protein, which is the most popular type of protein. Whey protein is made up of branched chain amino acids (BCAAs) and essential amino acids (EAAs), and has the highest biological value (the measure of how well your body absorbs and assimilates protein). The whey protein in NITRO-TECH is sourced primarily from whey peptides and whey isolate – two of the cleanest and purest protein sources available. Using these proteins on a daily basis is vital in helping to increase muscle protein synthesis for more muscle size and strength.

30g PROTEIN

What makes plant-based protein good?

If you are a committed vegetarian or vegan, or for some other reason (such as an intolerance) you prefer not to consume animal proteins, you will have to look into your options for plant-based protein sources. These, however, do not have a full amino acid profile as even if they contain all the essential amino acids, their relative ratio does not match human needs, as opposed to animal protein sources. As protein contributes to muscle growth and maintenance and to the maintenance of a normal bone structure*; it is necessary and important to consume an optimal amount of quality protein even if you lead a vegan lifestyle.

fields.name: OstroVit Creatine Monohydrate 300g
fields.description:
OstroVit Creatine Monohydrate is the highest-quality creatine monohydrate, which repeatedly enhances the anabolic, ergogenic and anti-catabolic effects of creatine.

Creatine is an organic chemical compound that occurs naturally in the human body. It is usually supplied with animal products, ie meat, eggs or fish. Its beneficial effect is based on a simple mechanism that releases energy in the form of high-energy ATP (adenosine triphosphate) molecules through the breakdown of phosphocreatine in the muscles. Despite the fact that creatine is also contained in food, the only one way to 100% saturate our muscles with creatine is to supplementate it constantly.
